By Onyebuchi Ezigbo Nigeria has continued to record high numbers of newly confirmed cases of Covid-19 with 1,024 new Infections reported on Sunday. A daily statistics of Covid-19 infection spread posted by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on its website showed that 1,024 new confirmed cases and eight deaths were recorded in Nigeria. The report showed that till date, 100,087 cases have been confirmed, 80,030 cases discharged and 1,358 deaths recorded in 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). The 1,024 new cases are reported from 17 states â€” Lagos (653), Plateau (63), Benue (48), Zamfara (45), FCT (42), Rivers (27), Ondo (26), Adamawa (26), Kaduna (22), Edo (18), Ogun (16), Imo (12), Kano (9), Yobe (6), Ekiti (5), Jigawa (4) and Osun (2).